truth handling

#axiom do not confuse poetry with truth

poetry may contain signal
but must be extracted before storage as core knowledge

pipeline

raw input
-> extract signal
-> normalize
-> assign state
-> store

⸻

noise handling

#axiom noise can carry signal

typos, compressed phrasing, and emotional language may still contain valuable meaning

rule

do not trust noisy input directly
do extract stable concepts from it

⸻

captain model

human remains captain

captain
-> defines intent
-> reviews ambiguity
-> verifies truth

system
-> extracts
-> organizes
-> compares
-> stores

compressed

captain decides
system assists

⸻

drift definition

#definition drift

a gradual loss of precision, correctness, or consistency caused by bad updates, incomplete replacements, or unverified changes

prevention
	•	compare before replace
	•	preserve better version
	•	do not overwrite verified truth casually

⸻

language philosophy

beast language assumes
	•	humans think in stories and compressed signals
	•	machines need stable tags and structure
	•	small primitives scale better than large grammars
	•	exact wording sometimes matters a lot

